<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="27" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,325,1249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
1. Hindwing ground color white or yellowish white, with no conspicuous dark marginal band (
<figureCitation box="[1188,1292,325,348]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[275,1305,212,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-177@4.[270,1316,197,1659]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Adults of Bergiantina, schausi group. 1. B. schausi, dorsal view; 2. B. schausi, ventral view; 3. B. intermedia, dorsal view; 4. B. intermedia, ventral view; 5. B. parva, dorsal view; 6. B. parva, ventral view; 7. B. trita, type, dorsal view; 8. B. dolens, type, dorsal view. Natural Size 1:1." pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Figs. 5–8</figureCitation>
); if hindwing ground color orange yellow, then marginal band not extending basally through costa (
<figureCitation box="[1111,1214,357,380]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[275,1305,212,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-177@4.[270,1316,197,1659]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Adults of Bergiantina, schausi group. 1. B. schausi, dorsal view; 2. B. schausi, ventral view; 3. B. intermedia, dorsal view; 4. B. intermedia, ventral view; 5. B. parva, dorsal view; 6. B. parva, ventral view; 7. B. trita, type, dorsal view; 8. B. dolens, type, dorsal view. Natural Size 1:1." pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Figs. 1–4</figureCitation>
). Valve of male genitalia increasing their size to the middle, apical half of right valve without depressions and apex rounded with one or two apical knobs (
<figureCitation box="[394,524,421,444]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–22" captionStartId="14.[151,270,1164,1188]" captionTargetBox="[160,1416,194,1127]" captionTargetId="figure-107@14.[160,1426,194,1161]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 18–22. Male genitalia of Bergiantina, schausi group. 18. B. schausi; 19. B. intermedia; 20. B. parva; 21. B. trita, type; 22. B. dolens, type. = carina; = knob; and = projection. Scale bars = 3 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Figs. 18–22</figureCitation>
). (
<taxonomicName box="[552,632,421,444]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Aucula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schausi">
<emphasis box="[552,632,421,444]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">schausi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group) .......................................................................................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,325,1249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
1’. Hindwing ground color orange yellow, with marginal band extending basally through costa (
<figureCitation box="[1182,1298,453,476]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–14" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1136,1160]" captionTargetBox="[252,1336,204,1110]" captionTargetId="figure-409@10.[245,1342,194,1114]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–14. Adults of Bergiantina, hilzingeri group. 9. B. hilzingeri, dorsal view; 10. B. hilzingeri, ventral view; 11. B. familiae, dorsal view; 12. B. familiae, ventral view; 13. B. magnifica, dorsal view; 14. B. magnifica, ventral view. Natural Size 1:1." pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Figs. 9–14</figureCitation>
); some specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[329,378,485,508]" name="Peru" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Peru</collectingCountry>
with hindwing white, only differentiable of the species of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1047,1127,485,508]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Aucula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schausi">
<emphasis box="[1047,1127,485,508]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">schausi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by its genitalia. Valve of male genitalia increase their size to the tip, apical half of right valve with a wide middle conical depression (medial notch) on ventral margin of valvula and apex flattened and ear-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1048,1179,549,572]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–26" captionStartId="14.[151,271,1923,1947]" captionTargetBox="[191,1401,1278,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-114@14.[184,1403,1277,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 23–26. Male genitalia of Bergiantina, hilzingeri group. 23. B. hilzingeri, showing group characters; 24. B." pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Figs. 23–26</figureCitation>
). (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berg" authorityYear="1882" box="[1206,1308,549,572]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Metagarista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilzingeri">
<emphasis box="[1206,1308,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">hilzingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group) ..... ...................................................................................................................................................................................... 6
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,325,1249]" box="[151,1435,613,636]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,613,636]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
2. Hindwing ground color orange yellow, with brown marginal band (
<figureCitation box="[917,1011,613,636]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[275,1305,212,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-177@4.[270,1316,197,1659]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Adults of Bergiantina, schausi group. 1. B. schausi, dorsal view; 2. B. schausi, ventral view; 3. B. intermedia, dorsal view; 4. B. intermedia, ventral view; 5. B. parva, dorsal view; 6. B. parva, ventral view; 7. B. trita, type, dorsal view; 8. B. dolens, type, dorsal view. Natural Size 1:1." pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Figs. 1–4</figureCitation>
)........................................................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,325,1249]" box="[151,1435,645,668]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,645,668]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
2’. Hindwing ground color white or yellowish white, with no conspicuous dark marginal band (
<figureCitation box="[1182,1279,645,668]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[275,1305,212,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-177@4.[270,1316,197,1659]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Adults of Bergiantina, schausi group. 1. B. schausi, dorsal view; 2. B. schausi, ventral view; 3. B. intermedia, dorsal view; 4. B. intermedia, ventral view; 5. B. parva, dorsal view; 6. B. parva, ventral view; 7. B. trita, type, dorsal view; 8. B. dolens, type, dorsal view. Natural Size 1:1." pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Figs. 5–8</figureCitation>
)................... 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,325,1249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
3. Forewing outer margin of postmedial line with three white distal patches: from costa to R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1156,1163,692,705]" fontSize="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">5</subScript>
, from M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1259,1266,692,705]" fontSize="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">1</subScript>
to M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1324,1331,692,705]" fontSize="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">3</subScript>
and from CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[249,256,726,739]" fontSize="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">2</subScript>
to A1 + A2 (
<figureCitation box="[407,554,712,735]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[275,1305,212,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-177@4.[270,1316,197,1659]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Adults of Bergiantina, schausi group. 1. B. schausi, dorsal view; 2. B. schausi, ventral view; 3. B. intermedia, dorsal view; 4. B. intermedia, ventral view; 5. B. parva, dorsal view; 6. B. parva, ventral view; 7. B. trita, type, dorsal view; 8. B. dolens, type, dorsal view. Natural Size 1:1." pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Figs. 1 and 2</figureCitation>
). Left plate of aedoeagus long, reaching the posterior end, with two lateral teeth, posterior greater than anterior one, and a greater terminal tooth (
<figureCitation box="[884,961,746,769]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–37" captionStartId="15.[151,270,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[227,1323,205,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-102@15.[219,1331,194,1886]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 27–37. Male aedeagi of Bergiantina, schausi group. 27. B. schausi; 28. B. intermedia; 29. B. parva; 30. B. trita, type; 31. B. dolens, type. 32–34. Details of the horn-like dorsal projection. 32. B. schausi; 33. B. intermedia; 34. B. parva; 35–37. Details of the right plate of the vesica. 35. B. schausi; 36. B. intermedia; 37. B. parva. Scale bar = 0.3 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) 
<emphasis box="[972,1192,746,769]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">.................................</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Jorgensen)" baseAuthorityName="Jorgensen" box="[1196,1436,746,769]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Aucula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schausi">
<emphasis box="[1196,1305,746,769]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">B. schausi</emphasis>
(Jörgensen)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,325,1249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
3’. Forewing outer margin of postmedial line with a continuous white strip only interrupted between CuA1-CuA2 (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[275,1305,212,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-177@4.[270,1316,197,1659]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Adults of Bergiantina, schausi group. 1. B. schausi, dorsal view; 2. B. schausi, ventral view; 3. B. intermedia, dorsal view; 4. B. intermedia, ventral view; 5. B. parva, dorsal view; 6. B. parva, ventral view; 7. B. trita, type, dorsal view; 8. B. dolens, type, dorsal view. Natural Size 1:1." pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Figs. 3 and 4</figureCitation>
). Left plate of aedoeagus short, not reaching the end and without tooth (
<figureCitation box="[1048,1127,810,833]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–37" captionStartId="15.[151,270,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[227,1323,205,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-102@15.[219,1331,194,1886]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 27–37. Male aedeagi of Bergiantina, schausi group. 27. B. schausi; 28. B. intermedia; 29. B. parva; 30. B. trita, type; 31. B. dolens, type. 32–34. Details of the horn-like dorsal projection. 32. B. schausi; 33. B. intermedia; 34. B. parva; 35–37. Details of the right plate of the vesica. 35. B. schausi; 36. B. intermedia; 37. B. parva. Scale bar = 0.3 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) 
<emphasis box="[1139,1350,810,833]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
......... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blas &amp; Navarro" authorityYear="2010" box="[1205,1350,810,833]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bergiantina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">B. intermedia</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1357,1436,810,834]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">sp nov.</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,325,1249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
4. Small, from 
<quantity box="[334,513,842,865]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6149999999999998" metricValueMax="1.67" metricValueMin="1.56" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="16.15" valueMax="16.7" valueMin="15.6">15.6 to 16.7 mm</quantity>
. Orbicular spot absent in some specimens and in other represented as a swelling of the antemedial line (
<figureCitation box="[377,440,874,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[275,1305,212,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-177@4.[270,1316,197,1659]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Adults of Bergiantina, schausi group. 1. B. schausi, dorsal view; 2. B. schausi, ventral view; 3. B. intermedia, dorsal view; 4. B. intermedia, ventral view; 5. B. parva, dorsal view; 6. B. parva, ventral view; 7. B. trita, type, dorsal view; 8. B. dolens, type, dorsal view. Natural Size 1:1." pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) 
<emphasis box="[453,1351,874,897]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
........................................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blas &amp; Navarro" authorityYear="2010" box="[1259,1351,874,897]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bergiantina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parva">B. parva</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1357,1436,874,898]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">sp nov.</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,325,1249]" box="[151,1435,906,929]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,906,929]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
4’. Bigger, from 
<quantity box="[343,522,906,929]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2199999999999998" metricValueMax="2.32" metricValueMin="2.12" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="22.2" valueMax="23.2" valueMin="21.2">21.2 to 23.2 mm</quantity>
. Orbicular spot black (
<figureCitation box="[764,892,906,929]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[275,1305,212,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-177@4.[270,1316,197,1659]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Adults of Bergiantina, schausi group. 1. B. schausi, dorsal view; 2. B. schausi, ventral view; 3. B. intermedia, dorsal view; 4. B. intermedia, ventral view; 5. B. parva, dorsal view; 6. B. parva, ventral view; 7. B. trita, type, dorsal view; 8. B. dolens, type, dorsal view. Natural Size 1:1." pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 7 and 8</figureCitation>
) ............................................................................. 5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,325,1249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
5. Forewing ground color dark greyish red, densely covered with white scales; discal cell white (
<figureCitation box="[1202,1267,938,961]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[275,1305,212,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-177@4.[270,1316,197,1659]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Adults of Bergiantina, schausi group. 1. B. schausi, dorsal view; 2. B. schausi, ventral view; 3. B. intermedia, dorsal view; 4. B. intermedia, ventral view; 5. B. parva, dorsal view; 6. B. parva, ventral view; 7. B. trita, type, dorsal view; 8. B. dolens, type, dorsal view. Natural Size 1:1." pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); horn-like dorsal projection of aedoeagus 1/3X as long as aedoeagus, rugous on the posterior side (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1181,970,993]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–37" captionStartId="15.[151,270,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[227,1323,205,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-102@15.[219,1331,194,1886]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 27–37. Male aedeagi of Bergiantina, schausi group. 27. B. schausi; 28. B. intermedia; 29. B. parva; 30. B. trita, type; 31. B. dolens, type. 32–34. Details of the horn-like dorsal projection. 32. B. schausi; 33. B. intermedia; 34. B. parva; 35–37. Details of the right plate of the vesica. 35. B. schausi; 36. B. intermedia; 37. B. parva. Scale bar = 0.3 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
) 
<emphasis box="[1192,1272,970,993]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">............</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Druce)" baseAuthorityName="Druce" box="[1277,1435,970,993]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Erocha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trita">
<emphasis box="[1277,1346,970,993]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">B trita</emphasis>
(Druce)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,325,1249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
5’. Forewing ground color brownish red, densely covered with white scales; discal cell as ground color (
<figureCitation box="[1290,1356,1002,1025]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[275,1305,212,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-177@4.[270,1316,197,1659]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Adults of Bergiantina, schausi group. 1. B. schausi, dorsal view; 2. B. schausi, ventral view; 3. B. intermedia, dorsal view; 4. B. intermedia, ventral view; 5. B. parva, dorsal view; 6. B. parva, ventral view; 7. B. trita, type, dorsal view; 8. B. dolens, type, dorsal view. Natural Size 1:1." pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); hornlike dorsal projection of aedoeagus 1/2X as long as aedoeagus, smooth (
<figureCitation box="[967,1044,1034,1057]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–37" captionStartId="15.[151,270,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[227,1323,205,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-102@15.[219,1331,194,1886]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 27–37. Male aedeagi of Bergiantina, schausi group. 27. B. schausi; 28. B. intermedia; 29. B. parva; 30. B. trita, type; 31. B. dolens, type. 32–34. Details of the horn-like dorsal projection. 32. B. schausi; 33. B. intermedia; 34. B. parva; 35–37. Details of the right plate of the vesica. 35. B. schausi; 36. B. intermedia; 37. B. parva. Scale bar = 0.3 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
) 
